This paper deals with the problem of finding a popular matching in a bipartite graph with preference lists, which is a classic problem in algorithmic game theory and computational social choice. The paper presents both hardness results and polynomial-time algorithms for different variants of the problem. This makes it relevant to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Among these, cs.DS and cs.GT are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on algorithmic and combinatorial aspects of the problem.
